Introduction

The Amazon rain forest plays a vital role in the earths climate system and global water cycle. It acts as a big carbon sink and contributes significantly to regional and global precipitation patterns through evapotranspiration. However, widespread deforestation driven by agriculture, logging, and urbanization threaten the Amazon rain forest. Changes in forest cover can disrupt water storage and availability, affecting surface water, soil moisture, and groundwater dynamics. By analyzing terrestrial water storage anomalies from GRACE/GRACE-FO data in relation to deforestation areas, I want to see if there is a quantifiable correlation between the two. In order to get a most complete picture of the situation, a relatively large area of interest is chosen:

# Zeitreihe erstellen fr Amplitude

years <- format(time(tws_rast), "%Y")
annual_amp <- tapp(tws_rast, years, fun = function(x) {
  if (all(is.na(x))) {
    return(NA)
  } else {
    return(max(x, na.rm = TRUE) - min(x, na.rm = TRUE))
  }
})

pixel_lm <- function(y) {
  if (all(is.na(y))) return(NA)

  model <- lm(y ~ t)
  return(coef(model)[2])  # Steigung = Trend pro Jahr
}

make_diverging_cols <- function(r, n = 101) {
  # Symmetrisch um 0
  zlim <- max(abs(range(values(r), na.rm = TRUE)))
  
  # Braun  Wei  Blau
  pal <- colorRampPalette(c("brown", "white", "blue"))(n)
  
  list(
    col = pal,
    range = c(-zlim, zlim)
  )
}

Data processing tree cover

process_MOD44B_treecover <- function(hdf_folder, aoi, output_file) {
  hdf_files <- list.files(hdf_folder, pattern = "\\.hdf$", full.names = TRUE)
  if(length(hdf_files) == 0) stop("Keine HDF-Dateien im Ordner gefunden!")

  tree_rasters <- lapply(hdf_files, function(f) {
    sds_path <- sprintf('HDF4_EOS:EOS_GRID:"%s":MOD44B_250m_GRID:Percent_Tree_Cover', f)
    rast(sds_path)
  })

  mosaic_tree <- do.call(mosaic, tree_rasters)
  
  if (!identical(crs(mosaic_tree), crs(aoi))) {
    aoi <- project(aoi, crs(mosaic_tree))
  }
  
  tree_crop <- crop(mosaic_tree, aoi)
  tree_masked <- mask(tree_crop, aoi)
  
  plot(tree_masked, main = paste("MOD44B Tree Cover -", output_file))
 # writeRaster(tree_masked, output_file, overwrite = TRUE)
  
  return(tree_masked)
}

make_diverging_cols_yellow_green <- function(r, n = 101) {
  # symmetrischer Wertebereich um 0
  zlim <- max(abs(range(values(r), na.rm = TRUE)))
  
  # Farbverlauf: negativ = gelb, 0 = wei, positiv = grn
  pal <- colorRampPalette(c("yellow", "white", "green"))(n)
  
  list(
    col = pal,
    range = c(-zlim, zlim)
  )
}

cols_tcc <- make_diverging_cols_yellow_green(tree_cover_change_resampled)

plot(
  tree_cover_change_resampled,
  main = "Tree Cover Change (resampled)",
  col  = cols_tcc$col,
  range = cols_tcc$range
)

plot(land_v, add = TRUE, border = "black", lwd = 1.5)

plot(countries_v, add = TRUE, border = "grey20", lwd = 0.5)

plot(lakes_v, add = TRUE, col = "lightblue", border = "lightblue")
plot(rivers_v, add = TRUE, col = "lightblue", lwd = 0.4)

png(
  filename = here::here("fig", "tree_cover_change_resampled.png"),

  res = 300
)

Correlation tree cover change & change in yearly TWS amplitude

# Korrelation

trend_map  <- trend_aoi
tree_map   <- mask(crop(tree_cover_change_resampled, polygon_vect), polygon_vect)

tree_map_resampled <- terra::resample(tree_map, trend_map)

vals <- cbind(
  trend = values(trend_map),
  tree  = values(tree_map_resampled)
)

vals <- vals[complete.cases(vals), ]
colnames(vals) <- c("trend", "tree")

correlation_result <- cor(vals[, "trend"], vals[, "tree"], method = "pearson")
lm_model <- lm(trend ~ tree, data = as.data.frame(vals))
lm_sum <- summary(lm_model)

png(
  filename = here::here("fig", "scatter_trend_vs_treecover.png"),
  width = 2000, height = 1500, res = 200
)

plot(vals[, "tree"], vals[, "trend"],
     xlab = "Tree cover change (20002024)",
     ylab = "TWS amplitude trend (yearly)",
     main = "Spatial correlation: TWS trend vs. Tree cover change")

abline(lm_model, col = "red", lwd = 2)

text(
  x = par("usr")[1] + 0.02 * diff(par("usr")[1:2]),
  y = par("usr")[4] - 0.02 * diff(par("usr")[3:4]),
  labels = sprintf(
    "Pearson r = %.3f\nSlope = %.3f\np-value = %.3g\nR = %.3f",
    correlation_result,
    lm_sum$coefficients["tree", "Estimate"],
    lm_sum$coefficients["tree", "Pr(>|t|)"],
    lm_sum$r.squared
  ),
  adj = c(0, 1), cex = 1.2
)

dev.off()
## png 
##   2
pred <- predict(lm_model, interval = "confidence")

ord <- order(vals[, "tree"])
tree_sorted <- vals[ord, "tree"]
pred_sorted <- pred[ord, ]

png(
  filename = here::here("fig", "scatter_trend_vs_treecover_95confidence.png"),
  width = 2000, height = 1500, res = 200
)

plot(vals[, "tree"], vals[, "trend"],
     xlab = "Tree cover change (20002024)",
     ylab = "TWS amplitude trend (yearly)",
     main = "Spatial correlation: TWS trend vs. Tree cover change (95% CI)")

  y = c(pred_sorted[, "lwr"], rev(pred_sorted[, "upr"])),
  col = adjustcolor("red", alpha.f = 0.2),
  border = NA
)

lines(tree_sorted, pred_sorted[, "fit"], col = "red", lwd = 2)

text(
  x = par("usr")[1] + 0.02 * diff(par("usr")[1:2]),
  y = par("usr")[4] - 0.02 * diff(par("usr")[3:4]),
  labels = sprintf(
    "Pearson r = %.3f\nSlope = %.3f\np-value = %.3g\nR = %.3f",
    correlation_result,
    lm_sum$coefficients["tree", "Estimate"],
    lm_sum$coefficients["tree", "Pr(>|t|)"],

  ),

)
